    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Problem\n\n`:restart` uses Nvim's current directory at the time of `:restart` instead of the one used during initial start (i.e. shell's directory). This can cause problems if Nvim is started with relative path as an argument.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. From the root of this repo start `nvim --clean LICENSE.txt`. It opens `LICENSE.txt` as expected.\n2. `:cd src`\n3. `:restart` - there is an empty buffer for `LICENSE.txt` and `:pwd` shows `path/to/repo/src`.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n`:restart` always uses initial current directory when restarting. Or at least `:restart` with relative path arguments resolves them relative to the initial working directory.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.13.0-dev-255+g61daad3bba\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nNo, doesn't have this functionality\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nEndeavourOS Linux x86_64, 6.19.11-arch1-1\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nGhostty 1.3.1-arch2\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-ghostty\n\n### Installation\n\nAppimage",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
